HEADWORD: Cumene
<hw>Cu"mene</hw> <pr>(k?"m?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Cumin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless oily
hydrocarbon, <chform>C6H5.C3H7</chform>, obtained by the distillation of
cuminic acid; -- called also <altname>cumol</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
